def find_gcd(n1, n2):
    while n2:
        n1, n2 = n2, n1 % n2
    return n1

This is a loop that continues as long as n2 is not zero.

import math

def find_gcd(n1, n2):
    return math.gcd(n1, n2)



ğŸ” First iteration:
n1 = 48, n2 = 18

n1 % n2 = 48 % 18 = 12

Now, update values:

n1 = 18, n2 = 12

ğŸ” Second iteration:
n1 = 18, n2 = 12
n1 % n2 = 18 % 12 = 6

Update:

n1 = 12, n2 = 6

ğŸ” Third iteration:
n1 = 12, n2 = 6

n1 % n2 = 12 % 6 = 0

Update:

n1 = 6, n2 = 0

Now the loop stops because n2 = 0.

âœ”ï¸ Answer: n1 = 6 is returned â†’ this is the GCD of 48 and 18.

ğŸ’¡ Summary of Logic:
Keep replacing:

n1 with n2

n2 with n1 % n2

Stop when n2 becomes 0

Return n1 (it will be the GCD)
